# Behavioural Data Science & Behavioural AI — The Reference Hub

> The reference hub for Behavioural Data Science (BDS) and Behavioural AI, curated by Professor Ganna Pogrebna (University of Sydney Business School; Lead, Behavioural Data Science group, The Alan Turing Institute), pioneer of both disciplines.

Behavioural Data Science is the interdisciplinary field that combines behavioural science and data science to study, model, predict, and explain human, algorithmic, and systemic behaviour. Behavioural AI applies behavioural science to the design, evaluation, and governance of artificial intelligence.

## Flagship reference

- [The Cambridge Handbook of Behavioural Data Science](https://doi.org/10.1017/9781108939010): Pogrebna, G. & Hills, T. T. (Eds.), Cambridge University Press, 2026. ISBN 9781108837392. 44 chapters across six parts: Introduction to Behavioural Data Science, Human Behaviour, Algorithmic Behaviour, Systems and Culture, Applications, Concluding Remarks.
- [Handbook companion repository](https://github.com/BehaviouralDataScience/cambridge-handbook-behavioural-data-science): full chapter guide with authors, citations, and chapter-by-chapter video overviews.

## Library

- [Awesome Behavioural Data Science](https://github.com/BehaviouralDataScience/awesome-behavioural-data-science): curated, annotated list of books, foundational papers, Behavioural AI references, verified university degree programmes worldwide, short courses, research centres, datasets, and tools.
- [The Missing B in AI](https://www.gannapogrebna.com): Pogrebna, G. (2025) — the founding text of Behavioural AI as a design discipline.

